## Competitive Landscape Quick Reference

When running Phase 2, start with these known competitors by domain:

### Technology Suite
- **Incident IQ** — direct competitor (ITAM, Help Desk, asset management)
- **Jamf** — adjacent (MDM, Apple device management; partnership angle)
- **Generic ITSM** — ServiceNow, Freshservice, etc. (not K-12 native)
- **CDW/Insight** — adjacent (procurement + lifecycle services)

### Facilities Suite
- **SchoolDude / Brightly (Siemens)** — direct competitor (work orders, schedules, utilities)
- **FMX** — direct competitor (facilities management, work orders)
- **Frontline Education** — adjacent (HR, absence, some facilities overlap)
- **Generic CMMS** — Fiix, UpKeep, Hippo, etc. (not K-12 native)

### Cross-Suite / Platform
- No known competitor currently spans both K-12 IT asset management AND facilities management in a unified platform — this is a potential differentiation angle.
